Aetherium Lite Runtime Repository Licensing

This repository is a mixed-license source and patch repository.

Original Aetherium glue files are licensed under the MIT License. That includes
repository documentation, manifests, and scripts written specifically for this
project, unless a file says otherwise.

Patch files and copied license texts follow the license of the upstream project
they modify or describe:

- third_party/proton-runtime/source-patches/proton: Proton upstream terms and
  bundled third-party licenses.
- third_party/proton-runtime/source-patches/box64: Box64 MIT License.
- third_party/proton-runtime/source-patches/wine: Wine LGPL-2.1-or-later.
- third_party/proton-runtime/source-patches/dxvk: DXVK zlib/libpng-style
  License.
- third_party/proton-runtime/source-patches/vkd3d-proton: vkd3d-proton
  LGPL-2.1.

Copies of upstream license files are stored under LICENSES/. The MIT text for
original Aetherium glue code is stored at LICENSES/aetherium/MIT.txt.

Do not treat this whole repository as MIT-only. Binary releases built from these
sources must keep notices for every bundled runtime component and must provide
corresponding source for LGPL-covered modified components such as Wine and
vkd3d-proton.
